content.htmlText:
Coconut Grove hugs the shoreline of Biscayne Bay. The streets are lined with palms and shady trees. The heart of the Grove has bars, restaurants, chic shops, galleries, sailing clubs, marinas, and more!
If nightlife is your scene, the Grove is only half an hour from Miami Beach, Wynwood, Downtown, and Bayside Marketplace as well! If you’re here for nature, Key Biscayne, Crandon Park, and Bill Baggs State Park are just a quick jaunt over the Rickenbacker Causeway, but be sure to stop at Vizcaya Museum & Gardens on your way. Just steps to the dog park and playground as well, you can walk your babies (and fur babies) before you head to Jungle Island and the Kids Museum, also about 20 minutes away. With both hidden/gated and street parking you’ll have room to show off your newly discovered hidden gem, a perfect Grove getaway for all of your South Florida adventures!!

reviews.comments: We always love our stay at Ari’s bungalows! Great communicator as well.

Ari’s place was such a cozy nook, covered by lots of lush plants and trees. The mango tree and patio made it even better! The property is tucked away and provides a lot of privacy. The house itself is exactly like the photos and extremely neat and clean. I loved the layout on the minimalist kitchen. Check-in and check-out was a very easy process. I would definitely recommend if you need to be in the coconut grove area and a travel with 1-4 people.
Ari has been great from start to finish.  His home is so private and peaceful. Super close to Coconut Grove.  Loved our stay here!

Cute bungalow in a great location.
Within walking distance to great restaurants, fun shopping and beautiful Biscayne Bay.
The house is very clean and comfortable. Added bonus is the courtyard where my dog could roam but was safe behind the fence. I’d like to stay here again on my next visit to Miami.

Clean, comfortable home
a nice walk to bars, restaurants, and shops.
Quiet, quaint, clean, comfortable and super convenient location. Ari was easy to communicate with, responsive and helpful.  We enjoyed our stay!
Thanks for the stay. It was a pleasure!
I cannot say enough great things about this wonderful place and our hosts. We were there for an entire month and felt right at home. Amazing location!
Love this place and location.  Hosts are very responsive.  We will be back next year!

This home is fantastic and Ari (host) was beyond helpful, responsive and thoughtful. We stayed for a full month and wish we could have been there longer!
The home sits in a very peaceful, safe part of Coconut Grove with easy access (5 minute walk) to CocoWalk as well as all of the restaurants and amenities in the Grove. The dog park across the street is beyond convenient and while we don't have kids, the playground across the street looked clean and always full of families. The house was clean and cozy and stocked with anything you could possibly need. The outside area, equipped with multiple seating areas and a covered, screened in patio, was great for a drink or morning coffee.
Ari always responded within minutes and was always willing to help.
Cannot recommend this home enough and can't wait to be back!
Clean, responsive host and walkable to various restaurants and shops, yet has a residential feel. Perfect for what we were looking for!

Ari's place is a peaceful getaway in Miami yet so close to all of the action. Conveniently situated walking distance from the restaurants of Coconut Walk, Ari's place a great place to stay during your vacation! Not only was the home private but also cozy, spacious and clean. There is a kids and dog park on the same street and everything you need to get to is 3-4 blocks away. The Nespresso machine was a lovely touch and the beds are super comfortable. However, the most important thing of this AirBnB was the host, Ari, who was responsive and kind to check in on us during our stay! I can't rave about this place enough!
It was a wonderful host and very good experience! Bed is so comfy and highly recommend!

We really enjoyed our stay. The location was great for walking to coffee, dinner, and our cruise into Biscayne National Park. The included parking spot(s) made having a rental car less stressful. The property was as described and the neighborhood is safe and quiet. We would stay again.

Ari’s place is perfectly situated in a quiet and nice area. Everything you need for a couple of days in the Grove. Communication and check-in were super-easy and we would love to come back! Highly recommended!

Ari’s place was just like the photos, a perfect little oasis in a quiet neighborhood in walking distance from the shops & restaurants in Coconut Grove. It’s was a bit hard to find when we arrived at night in the dark but otherwise it was perfect for us and our teenager. We’ll definitely be back!

Maison très propre, agréable quartier, calme, supermarché à cinq minutes, restaurants et magasins à dix minutes.
La pièce principale manque d'éclairage.
L'entrée est très sombre quand on arrive tard, un petit éclairage serait le bienvenu surtout pour voir la marche extérieure Nous avons eu quelques difficultés à entrer dans le logement car le code reçu n'était pas le bon mais l'hote a répondu très vite à nos messages. Nous n'avions pas de connexion internet et nous n'avions pas pu voir le second code envoyé tardivement.
Je recommande le logement. Hote très sympathique.

localizedReview.comments:
Very clean house, nice neighborhood, quiet, supermarket five minutes away, restaurants and shops ten minutes away.
The main room lacks lighting.
The entrance is very dark when we arrive late, a little lighting would be welcome especially to see the outside walk. We had some difficulty getting into the accommodation because the code received was not the right one but the host responded very quickly to our messages. We didn't have an internet connection and we couldn't see the second code sent late.
I would recommend the place. Very nice host.

reviews.comments: My family and I had a wonderful stay at Ari and Chana's place. It was ideally located close to many restaurants and had a park across the street, which my girls loved.  We enjoyed walking to dinner every night and seeing the locals out and about strolling with their children or dogs.  The place was great for us to come back to after  a day of exploring Miami and the national parks -- a great choice for families.
quiet haven but close to everything. neat and tidy and very well kept. we had a great stay.

This was probably one of my favorite Airbnb stays. I loved this house and location. Ari was super-friendly and communicative. The neighborhood is great, also loved it. An overall wonderful experience!
Lovely place that is in a great location!

For a family with a toddler and infant amazing location across from Blanche park. Quiet and easy. Ari was a great host and very responsive. 5 minute walk to downtown CG. The space is exactly what you see in photos. My go to spot in Miami from here on out.
Enjoyed our stay. Cute, clean secluded cottage within walking distance to downtown  Coconut Grove.

We loved it! I would go back. Just a delightful experience.
Thank you!!
Great place and easy walk to the Grove

Nous avons passé un excellent moment à Miami . La location se situe dans un quartier calme et agréable. Nous ne pouvons que conseiller cette location à tous ceux qui souhaitent passer du temps dans cette ville !

localizedReview.comments: We had a great time in Miami . The rental is located in a quiet and pleasant neighborhood. We can only recommend this rental to anyone who wants to spend time in this city!

reviews.comments:
This house was perfect!! Cozy and very well appointed. The hosts are wonderful, with excellent communication at all times. The location couldn’t be better!!! Just in front of a park, doggie park and a few blocks to Coco Walk.
Will definitely consider staying again and definitely will recommend it highly.

What a great stay! Was there for about a week. The place is clean, quiet, and exactly what we needed. Walking distance to the grove/shops/restaurants but still far enough to be peaceful. Loved having the screened porch outside and the privacy of the front and back yard. Great wifi for working from home. Thanks for an amazing stay, we will definitely be back.
We had a great stay at this adorable bungalow!  It was well-equipped and beautifully decorated. It felt private and secluded, yet just a short walk to the center of Coconut Grove.

Great experience! One the cleanest Airbnb’s I’ve stayed. It’s like having a private (and quite) bungalow oasis in Miami! Having your own parking spot felt glorious. Additionally, the interior has been tastefully renovated.
I would definitely stay again!

Aris Ferienhaus ist ein super Ort um in Miami unterzukommen. Es ist mit dem eigenen Innenhof, welcher einem Dschungel gleicht, total privat und ruhig. Zugleich ist man aber auch schnell in Downtown oder an einem der schönen Strände. Ari ist ein super Gastgeber, der immer erreichbar ist und absolut hilfreich zur Seite steht. Absolut empfehlenswert!

localizedReview.comments: Aris vacation home is a great place to stay in Miami. It is totally private and quiet with its own courtyard, which resembles a jungle. At the same time, you can also get to downtown or one of the beautiful beaches quickly. Ari is a great host who is always available and absolutely helpful. Absolutely recommended!

reviews.comments: Love the bungalow! I had an image of what staying in Coconut Grove Miami would be like.  Ari’s place embodies that vibe.

We stayed for a week while getting our son settled at UM. We’re new to Miami, and this location was a great place to base out of to explore so many different areas. Great food nearby, home was cute and very comfortable, Ari was easy to communicate with, we loved it!

Our stay at Grove Bungalow was wonderful. The house is clean and beautifully decorated. The sofas and beds were top-notch comfortable, and the kitchen was stocked with basic necessities, including beverages and coffee. Ari was attentive to our needs and a pleasure to talk to. Hope to be back some day:)
Ari and his home were great. Felt right at home and the location couldn’t be better . Best spot in the grove!
This was a beautiful spot located in the best area! It was clean, quiet and had everything we needed. I would highly recommend this place to anyone!
Beautiful home in a wonderful neighborhood. Extremely close to the wonderful shops at the grove. Very warm and cozy. Had a little rainy day in and it was perfect ❤️❤️❤️

We had a great stay at Ari’s place. The house is designed and kept up with loving care from the beautiful art to the appointed kitchen to the lush gardens. The neighborhood is beautiful and peaceful and a short walk to lovely restaurants and shops in coconut grove. We stayed with our infant and loved the combination of quiet and convenience and the playground right across the street! Ari was so kind and clear in his communication and gave us great local recommendations. I’d highly recommend this bungalow for anyone looking for a warm (feeling only, a/c was nice and crispy) friendly place to stay in Miami.
Ari was super helpful and responsive! The place was great and very conveniently located

What a lovely oasis in coconut grove. We loved this super private and stylish cottage!  The space was so tastefully decorated and so very comfortable. Top quality linens, towels etc. We really appreciate the location - walkable to Cocowalk etc, while being behind the high fenced in, tropical yard felt like we were in our own little oasis. Spotlessly clean and super responsive and friendly host. Thank you so much Ari!!

Words aren’t enough. Truly my best trip in Miami and I would say that Ari’s location was at least half the reason why. I spent the weekdays working but even those felt like vacation due to the location I was in. To anyone I know visiting Miami, this is the only place I would recommend staying.
Beautiful home! Super clean, easy smooth check in/out, great location. We loved the screened in porch area. Would highly recommend!

Ari’s place was just gorgeous, small but perfect. Very very clean, beds were nice and comfortable and linens of top quality. It really exceeded all of our expectations in every sense: cleaning, confort, location, etc
Walking distance to all of what coconut grove has to offer and in front of a kids and dogs park. He answered us right away.
I will recommend Ari’s place to friends and family that come to visit Miami.

Gorgeous house in a lovely neighbourhood in Miami. Coconut Grove is quiet, calm + the streets are so pretty, lined with a canopy of tropical trees. The house is actually even better than the photos! Everything that's needed - luxury furnishings, bedding, towels etc. I highly recommend this house for a relaxing visit to Miami. Ari is a lovely host, Thanks for everything.

Our family had an amazing 5-night stay in Coconut Grove. The space was clean and tidy and the grounds were lush and tropical. We have 2 young kids and the fenced in courtyard felt safe for them to play in while we relaxed and had a drink. The kitchen has everything you would need to cook a meal - bonus points for a Nespresso w/pods! The playground across the street was super convenient. Everything was walkable (5-10 min to amazing restaurants and entertainment). Ari and Chana were super responsive if we had any questions and happily hopped on a call.
Highly recommend to any couples or young families looking to explore the area. Already planning our next trip back! Thanks again for having us :)
reviews.response: Appreciate all the feedback! You’ll see almost all of this in place and addressed when you come back. Cheers 🍻!!

reviews.comments: Ari’s bungalow was very good and I greatly enjoyed my stay. Felt like a home away from home. Ari was flexible to answer my call when I had a little trouble getting into the gate. I absolutely loved my stay and loved the bungalow. Thank you so much!
What a cozy stay in the heart of the grove.  Ari was exceptionally hospitable and went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we needed during our stay.  Don’t hesitate to book this gem.

Lovely Dreamhouse in Coconut Grove. I have been a host and a guest for a very long time and I really believe this is one of my favorite accommodations ever! Ari and Chana were both so hospitable and helpful from the moment we booked onwards.  I’m ready to move in really but Leif and Austin holds me back! However, my brother has recently moved to Miami, and I hope to visit him often. I could go on and on about the loveliness, but primarily the light, the privacy, the ease of parking, the plush linens and comforters, the sweet kitchen that was perfect for our needs, the amazing landscaped backyard, with so much greenery and sweetness, the park next door that was perfect for my kiddos when Mom needed some downtime……and more. Thank you again for having us Ari and Chana, we will be back without a doubt.
What a treasure!  It was the perfect place to stay for our Coconut Grove visit Close to regatta activities and our oasis to sit back and relax.  We will definitely be back.
Ari’s place was very clean, thoughtfully designed, in a great area, and the hosts are so thoughtful and kind. It would be hard to find a better place in Miami!
Very secluded feel, but close to downtown and U of Miami.

Ari and Chana’s Coconut Grove Bungalow is nothing short of EXCELLENT!
We were a group of three adults and one toddler. The space was perfect: comfortable, well appointed, and with a lovely garden. The location is on a peaceful tree-lined street within easy walking distance to downtown Coconut Grove and it’s directly across the street from a playground and dog run. When we travel we often stay at airbnbs and this one really stood out. Could not have been more pleased with our stay. Ari and Chana are also super responsive and kind people.
We hope to be back soon.

One of the best Airbnbs I ever stayed at! The space is tastefully decorated, very clean and had every amenity we needed for a long weekend stay. The location is also amazing and the hosts are very friendly. Would highly recommend this Airbnb.

Staying in a place without any reviews is a gamble, but this was probably my favorite airbnb that I have ever stayed in. As soon I opened the gate I knew I was somewhere magical. It feels like a secret jungle garden, with all kinds of different trees, ferns, palm trees. The house was so clean and felt extremely peaceful and uplifting to be in. Ari was the best host - welcoming and  very easy to communicate with. The location couldn’t be better - close enough to all the restaurants and shops in Coconut Grove to be able to easily walk, but far enough away that it felt quiet and private. And coming with a dog, having the nicest dog park next door was an unexpected nice bonus. I hope Ari’s place is available every time I come to Miami because I couldn’t imagine a better one.
